interdiction of drugs smuggled into the united states 
but the us administration has been criticized for its dealings 
with panamanian strongman gen manuel noriega indicted in the 
united states for drug trafficking and for not cracking down on 
governments that allow domestic drug production 
in her speech mrs reagan emphasized the need for police to 
arrest and for courts to punish all drug users it is as important 
to stop drug use in the united states she said as it is to stop 
cocagrowing in peru processing in colombia and shipping through 
the caribbean 
it is the united states alone which bears responsibility for 
its own drug problem she said while most of the illegal drugs 
are imported the drug users are homegrown 
if we lack the will to fully mobilize the forces of law in our 
own country to arrest and punish drug users if we cannot stem the 
american demand for drugs mrs reagan said then there will be 
little hope of preventing foreign drug producers from fulfilling 
that demand 
