capacity with 65 passengers and a crew of four slammed into a flood 
plain a minute after takeoff 
aeroperu spokesman freddy chirinos said 44 people were injured 
one person was unaccounted for he said 
many victims died from burns suffered after the plane split in 
three pieces on impact and the tail section burst into flames 
officials said wreckage was scattered across a half acre of pasture 
and a riverbed 
the jet had taken off from the manco capac airport in juliaca 
which is more than 12000 feet above sea level near lake titicaca in 
southern peru 
chirinos said at least 19 foreigners mainly tourists returning 
from the lake were aboard the craft flight 771 was en route to 
lima 540 miles northwest with a stop in arequipa 
aeroperu identified the foreign dead as douglas harris of the 
united states kurt lenz of switzerland and ervert and ingeborg 
psiller of france it gave no hometowns for the victims 
survivors and witnesses on the ground said the aircraft lost 
altitude seconds into the flight but regained it before crashing 
alongside the cabanillas river one mile northwest of the airport 
transportation minister camilo carrillo told reporters in juliaca 
that pilot fernando bellina who survived averted greater disaster 
by swerving the stricken craft to avoid a hill and crash landing on 
flood plain sand which absorbed some of the impact 
congressman rolando avila another survivor said the aircraft 
had flown only about 400 yards after takeoff when an explosion shook 
it and the jets cut off 
the pilots apparently tried to level off to land and the plane 
scraped the roofs of some adobe homes before falling he said 
airline officials would not speculate on what caused the crash 
they said an investigation was under way 
cesar atala a director of the pilots association of aeroperu 
said the union might call a strike today to protest airline 
maintenance practices he reiterated the associations charge that 
aeroperus fleet of 10 jetliners is in poor shape due to a shortage 
of spare parts 
but johnny cabrere an aeroperu air cargo employee in new york 
said flights were operating today were operating normally he 
said 
peru suffering through a severe economic crisis is virtually 
out of dollar reserves to import spare parts for much of its 
industry 
the last major air accident in peru occurred dec 9 when a 
twinengine navy fokker f27 crashed off limas pacific coast 
killing 44 people including nearly the entire squad of perus 
leading soccer team alianza lima 
chirinos identified the injured foreigners as elizabeth dunning 
catherine kanskey francois savoir michael reilly bernard mahoney 
and mark kranki of the united states luana and rafael gianinazzi of 
italy albert koyson and brigitte kahson of france walter kabin of 
great britain joacy borge of brazil and esther and ana lopez and 
gina garfias of spain 
the us embassy said it had no information on dead or injured 
americans 
