government off the backs of the american people part of that 
campaign included proposals to abolish the two newest cabinet 
departments energy and education 
those plans have long since been dropped and the departments are 
flourishing bureaucracies 
the senate recently gave final approval of a new department of 
veterans affairs in effect elevating the veterans administration to 
cabinet status 
each time a cabinet department is added it means new and often 
duplicated expense and with the new status the departments begin 
to grow far beyond their previous bounds 
of course in an election year its not likely that anybody would 
oppose creation of a department of veterans affairs that might 
smack of being antiveteran 
what we are likely to see is a new tangle of rules and 
regulations as the bureaucrats carve out their niches in the new 
department 
and veterans like nonveterans will help foot the bill through 
taxes 
