portland maine press herald on banning plastic firearms 
no one is manufacturing allplastic firearms yet but the 
technology is available and its only a matter of time 
given that prospect congress acted prudently last week in 
approving a ban on firearms capable of evading detection by metal 
detectors or xray machines 
the measure is a necessity it bans the manufacture importation 
sale shipment or possession of any firearm containing less than 37 
ounces of stainless steel exclusive of parts and magazines 
without this sort of legislation it would be possible for 
terrorists and other criminals to smuggle concealed weapons through 
detection devices at airports or courtrooms 
with it the job of law enforcement officials is enhanced 
the measure is a sensible one far better to confront the problem 
now before undetectable plastic firearms are on the market and on 
the street 
