<TEXT>
a committee of educators students and 
religious leaders has begun compiling a list of values to be taught 
in new jersey schools starting with honesty compassion courage 
and hard work 
the difficulty will be figuring out what else there is said 
gov thomas h kean who ordered the group to come up with its 
recommendations by march 
kean announced his valueseducation campaign earlier this year 
the committee began its work tuesday 
were all aware of the fact this effort is going to be complex 
and is a little controversial said richard herold a lawyer and 
chairman of the 20member panel 
new jersey joins other states including maryland california and 
new york working to bring values into public education despite 
wariness that it could violate constitutional principles of 
separation of church and state 
the trend has been applauded by conservative groups as well as 
the civil liberties organization people for the american way which 
endorses values education as long as tolerance is one of the lessons 
stressed 
there has been a growing consensus that students arent born 
knowing the difference between right and wrong any more than theyre 
born with the knowledge of calculus said david crane education 
issues director for people for the american way based in 
washington dc 
kean a republican lamented such disgraced national figures as 
former white house aide michael deaver and wall street giant ivan 
boesky 
good citizenship kean said is as important to teach as english 
and chemistry 
what teachers tell me and counselors tell me again and again is 
there doesnt seem to be anything these youth can put their faith 
in kean said adding that amoral young people are easy marks 
for drug dealers 
values would not be taught in a single class but would be laced 
through the curriculum from elementary grades to high school 
education commissioner saul cooperman said 
he suggested young students could be taught the sacredness of 
promises for example while older students could learn about the 
importance of crediting sources in english papers 
details such as whether students would be graded on the values 
they learn have yet to be determined 
teachers and administrators would have to teach by example 
cooperman said 
we cant say do as i say but dont do as i do he said 
kids see through that in five seconds 
the panel chosen by cooperman represents a wide range of 
geography and backgrounds and includes a rabbi baptist minister and 
catholic bishop the only thing the members have in common is their 
own good citizenship kean said 
