meaning of independence 
he said the elections should inspire voteless people in south 
africa and in southwest africa or namibia which is ruled by south 
africa 
the congress of the united national independence party has 
routinely nominated kaunda the sole candidate since independence 
although it is free to choose more than one new elections are held 
if the sole candidate loses 
analysts expected a low turnout for the sixth postindependence 
elections but long lines had formed outside some polling stations 
in the capital lusaka before voting began at 6 am 
rural zambians went to the polls by bus bicycle tractor and on 
foot in some areas voters paddled canoes to the booths in the 
mpika district of central province where roads are impassable 
because of heavy rains voters were ferried by helicopters 
but zambian reporters in several rural areas said polling was 
slow and there were small lines outside most booths 
when kaunda led zambia to independence his people enjoyed one of 
the highest standards of living in africa thanks largely to high 
world prices for copper which earns 90 percent of export income 
but when prices slumped in the 1970s a time when landlocked 
zambia had transformed from food exporter to importer the nations 
fortunes changed the foreign debt mounted and today stands at 5 
billion 
most foreign donors have stopped helping zambia since kaunda last 
year abandoned an economic recovery program proposed by the 
international monetary fund 
