fund including scholarships and loan forgiveness for prospective 
teachers favors a 45 million effort to bring retired scientists 
and engineers into classrooms as teachers or aides opposes 
organized prayer in public schools 
congress has just voted to allow families to earn interest 
taxfree on us savings bonds for college tuition bush proposed 
such a move last year he wants to award unfettered grants of up to 
100000 to merit schools that succeed in spurring achievement 
of disadvantaged students would seek 50 million in matching grants 
for magnet schools would quadruple to 50 million a new federal 
fund to spur school innovations supports organized but voluntary 
prayer in public schools 
</TEXT>
