from bush while the presidential contest seemed to be giving 
marginal boosts to republican hopefuls in a few states it appears 
far short of the kind of sweep that gave the gop senate control in 
1980 when a 12seat shift accompanied reagans landslide white 
house win 
its not like 1980 when there was a need among voters to voice 
change said tom mason communications director for the republican 
national senatorial committee 
robert a chlopak executive director of the democratic 
