<TEXT>
four major commercial banks have asked the 
federal reserve board for broad powers to underwrite and deal in 
corporate securities after congress failed to pass legislation 
granting such authority 
the applications by citicorp chase manhattan corp jp morgan 
amp co and bankers trust new york corp were sent to the new york 
federal reserve bank on tuesday according to a fed spokesman 
banking experts say they expect most other big banks to follow 
suit 
if congress cant agree to do it the banks will attempt every 
possibility they can don ogilvie an executive vice president 
with the american bankers association said wednesday 
the move by the four banks could set the stage for a battle 
between congress and the fed over which body will determine the 
future structure of the banking industry 
fed chairman alan greenspan has supported banks efforts to win 
broader securities powers and manuel johnson a fed governor said 
recently that the central bank would look favorably on bank 
applications for greater securities powers if congress adjourned 
without passing legislation 
attempts by congress to repeal the depressionera glasssteagall 
act which separates commercial and investment banking have been 
underway for six years 
the most promising bill by william proxmire dwis and chairman 
of the senate banking committee died in the house along with more 
restrictive bill passed by the house banking committee 
after it appeared his bill was doomed proxmire encouraged banks 
to turn to the fed for broader powers 
in their applications citicorp chase morgan and bankers trust 
sought permission to underwrite and deal in corporate debt 
chase morgan and bankers trust also sought permission to deal 
and underwrite stock with chase and bankers trust adding preferred 
stock to their wish list 
two weeks ago chase president thomas labrecque had vowed to seek 
fed approval if efforts to pass legislation failed 
banks have maintained that they need expanded powers to compete 
with foreign banks that can underwrite securities in this country 
while critics maintain such powers could endanger the safety of the 
nations banking system 
last spring the us supreme court upheld a lower court ruling 
that allowed the fed to grant more than a dozen banks authority to 
underwrite commercial paper municipal revenue bonds 
mortgagebacked securities and securties backed by consumer loans 
