president richard d kinder said some of the reductions will be 
effective immediately while others will occur during the remainder 
of the year 
enron has about 6900 employees including 3000 in houston 
the cuts include jobs at all levels including officers human 
resources vice president luther snow is one executive whose position 
was eliminated the action follows the elimination of about 35 jobs 
in enron oil amp gas co a subsidiary in late september 
kinder said enron expects the reorganization to save 15 million 
a year 
it is not a pleasant thing to do but you cant operate in this 
environment without paying attention to your staff costs he said 
some of the affected employeees may be offered other jobs in the 
enron organization others will receive severance pay and assistance 
in finding jobs elsewhere 
