efforts to acquire fruehauf though he didnt rule out discussions 
about its kelseyhayes automotive subsidiary 
fruehauf has struggled with large debts high interest payments 
and operating losses in its trailer and maritime operations since 
managers took control of the company in december 1986 with huge 
borrowings in a financial transaction known as a leveraged buyout 
fruehauf will continue to explore alternatives including 
disposition of all or part of kelseyhayes its only profitable 
unit fruehauf spokesman david hladik said 
hladik said he knew of no specific suitors but even during 
discussions with varity we never closed the door to other 
offers 
formerly called masseyferguson torontobased varity makes farm 
and industrial machinery fruehauf makes truck trailers and 
automotive and maritime products 
varity ended discussions with fruehauf after a review of 
fruehaufs records and assets nowling said 
