<TEXT>
trans world airlines inc and pan am corp on wednesday reported 
increases in their thirdquarter profit from a year earlier while 
usair group incs net income was reduced by merger costs 
new yorkbased twa said its net income in the three months ended 
sept 30 jumped 544 percent to 88 million or 239 a share from 
571 million or 141 a share a year earlier 
thirdquarter revenue was up 49 percent to 127 billion from 
121 billion 
twa the nations seventhlargest airline was taken private on 
monday by its chairman and owner carl icahn 
lawsuits against the privatization have been filed by some twa 
shareholders and the pilots union at the airline in addition the 
union representing twa flight attendants has asked the department of 
transportation to block the privatization and freeze the airlines 
assets while it investigates icahns fitness to continue managing 
twa 
the twa pilots union joined the flight attendants petition and 
the consumer federation of america has filed a similar petition with 
the dot 
twa general counsel mark buckstein said recently that the carrier 
plans to lease or buy about 60 new aircraft to upgrade its aging 
fleet at a cost of up to 15 billion 
in the first nine months of the year twas profit more than 
doubled to 1327 million or 289 a share from 552 million 
or 45 cents a share a year earlier 
the latest ninemonth profit includes a special gain of 499 
million from a cash payment awarded to twa in a longstanding 
lawsuit against its former owner the late howard hughes 
the twa managements suit originally filed in 1962 alleged that 
the eccentric multimillionaire failed to provide the carrier with 
adequate aircraft although a delaware court decided in twas favor 
last year the payment was not made until the second quarter of 1988 
revenue in the first nine months rose 777 percent to 333 
billion from 309 billion 
pan am also based in new york said its thirdquarter net income 
edged up 63 percent helped by continuing improvement in profits 
from its northeast shuttle and pan am express commuter operations 
the eighthlargest us airline reported that its profit in the 
three months ended sept 30 rose to 674 million or 47 cents a 
share from 634 million or 45 cents a share a year earlier 
thirdquarter revenue expanded 137 percent to 120 billion 
from 106 billion 
the company said the growth in revenue was boosted by strong 
passenger traffic 
in fact pan am set a new quarterly record for revenue 
surpassing the levels reported during the time when the airline was 
operating its pacific division chairman thomas plaskett said 
in the first nine months of the year pan am had a net loss of 
210 million widened from a loss of 198 million a year earlier 
the loss occurred despite a 169 percent rise in revenue for the 
nine months to 318 billion from 272 billion 
washingtonbased usair said its thirdquarter profit was trimmed 
45 percent by expenses related to its acquisitions of piedmont 
aviation and pacific southwest airlines 
the nations ninthbiggest airline saw its net income slip to 
685 million or 158 a share from 717 million or 166 a 
share a year earlier 
the decline occurred despite an 873 percent jump in 
thirdquarter revenue to 148 billion from 7908 million 
in the first nine months usairs profit fell to 1422 million 
or 328 a share from 1679 million or 480 a share 
ninemonth revenue surged to 422 billion from 187 billion 
